blocks: <p>Maybe pronouns are needed to indicate everyone <em><strong>Except</strong></em> a given person? That is, single words to represent:<br /></p><ul><li>everybody-but-me</li><li>everybody-but-you</li><li>everybody-but-her/him/it</li></ul><p>... and so forth? That way, a speaker can more easily and precisely indicate who is <em><strong>not</strong></em> included in a generalization, who lacks a certain quality, etc. &mdash; making for more compact and precise expression. And it completes the logical Venn diagram of possible references in a useful way.</p><p>Yes, and maybe everybody-but-me sees no need for that ...</p><p><em><strong>^z</strong></em> - 2015-10-26</p>
