text: Maybe pronouns are needed to indicate everyone //**Except**// a given person? That is, single words to represent:
	* everybody-but-me
	* everybody-but-you
	* everybody-but-her/him/it
	
	... and so forth? That way, a speaker can more easily and precisely indicate who is //**not**// included in a generalization, who lacks a certain quality, etc. &mdash; making for more compact and precise expression. And it completes the logical Venn diagram of possible references in a useful way.
	
	Yes, and maybe everybody-but-me sees no need for that ...
	
	//**^z**// - 2015-10-26
	
